# Phase 0: Preprocessing

Prepare source materials for processing.

## Objective

Prepare and organize all source materials in `/1-input/` for subsequent processing phases.

## Tasks

### Source Preparation
- Gather all source materials
- Convert to processable format if needed
- Organize in logical structure within `/1-input/`

### Validation
- Verify all sources are complete and readable
- Check for any corrupted or missing files
- Document any source quality issues

### Documentation
- Create inventory of all source materials
- Note any preprocessing transformations applied
- Document source metadata (dates, authors, versions)

## Outputs

- Organized source materials in `/1-input/`
- Source inventory document
- Preprocessing notes (if any transformations applied)

## Completion Criteria

- [ ] All source materials gathered and organized
- [ ] Sources validated for completeness
- [ ] Inventory documented
- [ ] Ready for Phase 1 analysis
